page.title: 17TRAVEL THROUGH CATTERICK
page.content: The parish of Catterick with Tunstall is very popular with visitors. Both villages have beautiful churches, lovingly cared for by faithfull worshipers. Inside the churches are kept in pristine condition and the church yards are always well tended. Catterick is situated just off the A1 motorway, tourists heading for Yorkshires upper dales take the road through Catterick and Tunstall. This takes them along by the stream and Low Green, named so as Catterick has a High Green too. The stream, known locally as the beck, is a great attraction to picnicers as are the two public houses conveniently placed at both ends of the green. Tunstall's public house boasts a quoits team and this attracts a great many spectators on summer evenings.
